<p>I am trying to concatenate a variable to an array key to get access to certain values in Twig, but no success so far.</p>  <p>I have a large PHP array that has for example keys like this:</p>  <pre><code>$array = [    ...    ...    ...    'test_1' =&gt; $test_1,    'test_2' =&gt; $test_2 ]; </code></pre>  <p>I tried the following in my Twig template:</p>  <pre><code>{% for i in 1..2 %}     {% if array.test_{{ i }} != 0 %}       &lt;div&gt;Test&lt;/div&gt;    {% endif %}  {% endfor %} </code></pre>  <p>but that doesn't work.</p>  <p>Is there a way to access values like this in Twig?</p>